project IntervalMerge

task MergeOverlappingIntervals
    goal
        Merge overlapping and touching intervals into a sorted list of disjoint intervals.
    input
        intervals
    output
        merged
    constraint
        Function name is merge_intervals.
        Module is impl.py.
        Return value is a list of two-element lists.
        Result is sorted by start ascending.
        Intervals with equal endpoints are treated as touching and are merged.
    test
        Empty input returns empty output.
        A single interval is returned unchanged.
        Two overlapping intervals merge into one.
        Two touching intervals merge into one.
        A batch with a gap yields two intervals.
        Unsorted input is sorted before merging.
        The canonical LeetCode example merges correctly.
        Non-list input raises TypeError.
        An interval whose start exceeds its end raises ValueError.
        A non-two-element sub-list raises ValueError.
    success
        Every acceptance case above matches exactly.
